  "texts": [
    "The categories mentioned above of explainable recommendations relate to understanding the subject matter within cognitive psychology, as noted by Lipton (2018) and Miller (2019).",
    "Inherently explainable learning models may be associated with the fact that, as humans, we conscientiously evaluate all options before reaching decisions and employ suitable logic to ascertain the rationale behind our choices (Miller, 2019).",
    "On the other hand, model agnostic or post-hoc explanations may be associated with the tendency to generate explanations after reaching a conclusion.",
    "This type of methodology facilitates the process of rationalizing or refuting the decision (Lipton, 2018; Miller, 2019).",
    "XAI is not only limited to explainable recommendations but also to natural language processing, recommender systems, autonomous systems, computer visions, data-driven decision-making, reinforcement learning, and interpretable machine learning."
